headline: Only 16% of Largest Companies on Track for Net Zero Goals with Nearly Half Seeing Increased Emissions, Accenture Analysis Finds
summary: NEW YORK, November 11, 2024--Only one in six (16%) of the world’s largest companies are currently on track to reach net zero emissions in their operations by 2050.
